key: drop = obvious population structure in qqplot
ok = close to expected line but does not have a signal bump at high -log10pvalues
signal = signal bump in the highest -log10pvalues
nice = at least one 'peaky' region with high -log10pvalues
structure = many p-values at the same height on manhattan. Pop structure issue
centromere = at least one 'peaky' region in a pericentromeric region
skip = drop because of pop structure or low signal or iffy qqplot
